programme.title: Picnic at Hanging Rock
programme.desc: Mademoiselle De Poitiers, who was in charge of the girls at the picnic, is plagued by guilt, and students continue to be withdrawn from the college. Meanwhile, the French governess discovers Sara is missing from class and grows suspicious when she is informed that the young orphan has been unexpectedly collected by her guardian(n)

programme.title: Sylvia
programme.desc: Biopic of troubled poet and novelist Sylvia Plath whose creativity was deeply affected by her long and ultimately futile battle with depression. The film explores the impact of her mental state on her turbulent marriage to Ted Hughes, culminating in her eventual downward spiral into despair. Starring Gwyneth Paltrow, Daniel Craig, Jared Harris and Amira Casar(n)

credits.actor: Gwyneth Paltrow, Daniel Craig, Jared Harris, Amira Casar

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two(n)

programme.title: Gardeners' World
programme.desc: Monty Don looks at how his autumn crops are faring as well as giving tips on how to keep the garden looking at its best. Adam Frost returns to Leicester where he has been helping to create a garden from scratch on a new build estate, Frances Tophill celebrates the summer harvest on her shared allotment, and Mark Lane takes a look at the Mediterranean planting at Ventnor Botanic Garden on the Isle of Wight. The programme also visits Burton-on-Trent, Staffordshire, where an immaculate and tiny garden is packed with colour(n)

programme.title: Countryfile
programme.desc: The show comes from East Yorkshire, where John Craven meets Bridlington residents who take traditional coble boats out to sea, Margherita Taylor uncovers a secret art trail in the Wolds and meets poet Ian MacMillan, and Steve Brown learns about different uses for hemp. Plus, Charlotte Smith reports on the impact of tourism on beauty spots and Adam Henson meets a farmer with an active online presence(n)

programme.title: European Championships 2018
programme.desc: Hazel Irvine presents live coverage of day 11 from Glasgow and Berlin, featuring diving, open water swimming, road cycling, golf, and athletics. Both the women's and men's marathons are due to take place on the streets of the German capital this morning, and Great Britain's Callum Hawkins will be looking to perform well in the latter, especially so after collapsing during the men's race at the Commonwealth Games earlier this year. Meanwhile, Glasgow plays host to the men's 10m platform preliminary diving, the women's and men's 25km open water swimming races at Loch Lomond, the men's cycling road race, and the concluding day of the golf event at Gleneagles(n)

programme.title: Hairy Bikers' Best of British
programme.desc: Si King and Dave Myers celebrate British pork, preparing a traditional gala pie and a rolled loin with apricots and ginger. They also explore the role the pig has played in the UK's history and travel to a farm in Gloucestershire to visit a couple raising rare breeds(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.sub-title: The Mating Game - Natural World Special
programme.desc: David Attenborough narrates a look at the different methods animals use to attract a mate, revealing how inventive, loving and complex they can be. A female polar bear tries to revive a male's interest in her by turning cartwheels in front of him, while a bird of paradise tidies obsessively as he prepares a stage for his dance. While other lemurs are fighting for the right to breed, one sidles up to a female and wins favour by wafting his scent at her, and silverback gorilla seduction involves staring with a fixed grin(n)

programme.title: Money for Nothing
programme.desc: The team transform items reclaimed from a skip in Walsall in the West Midlands, featuring a leather chair, metal shoe lasts and four kitchen chairs(n)

programme.title: Escape to the Country
programme.desc: A couple with a passion for dogs and horses seek a dream country home in Norfolk for £850,000. Sonali Shah tries to find them a property with enough land for their animals and also visits a unique collection of vintage engines, organs and fairgound rides(n)

programme.title: European Championships 2018
programme.desc: Gabby Logan presents continued live coverage of day 11 from Glasgow and Berlin, featuring gymnastics, golf, and athletics. The men's individual apparatus gymnastics finals are due to come to a conclusion at The SSE Hydro, featuring the parallel bars and high bar disciplines, while the winners are decided in the ladies and men's golf competitions at Gleneagles. Meanwhile, the final night of the athletics competition is scheduled to commence at Olympiastadion Berlin with the final of the men's pole vault, and the opening round of the women's 4x100m relay(n)

programme.title: Mortimer & Whitehouse: Gone Fishing
programme.desc: Cameras follow old friends Paul Whitehouse and Bob Mortimer as they continue on their angling trip round the UK. This time, Paul and Bob fish the river Wensum in Norfolk for Roach, but as the pair struggle up and down the riverbanks, they begin to realise how age is starting to take its toll on their physicality. After staying overnight in a disused train station and visiting a local pub, the pair decide to challenge each other to a fishing competition the following day, where the winner gets a very special culinary treat(n)

programme.title: Inside the Factory
programme.desc: Gregg Wallace explores the North Yorkshire factory that produces 625,000 sausages a day, and Cherry Healey is at the University of Chester, getting the scientific lowdown on the best bangers. Plus, Ruth Goodman investigates how a German bratwurst became so popular in America(n)

programme.title: Dragons' Den
programme.desc: New series. Entrepreneurs Deborah Meaden, Peter Jones, Touker Suleyman, Tej Lalvani and Jenny Campbell assess more unusual business ideas, including a shocking display from the owner of a live anatomy dissection business and a new model of tuk-tuk that turns out to have a fatal flaw. The final presentation is for a singer-for-hire scheme, which prompts the panel to show off their own musical talents(n)

programme.title: Travels in Trumpland with Ed Balls
programme.desc: Ed Balls discovers who benefits financially from Trump's presidency, paying a visit to his private members' club, where a party is being held to mark the first anniversary of the election victory. He also meets a controversial pastor who believes prayer can lead to wealth and a musician attempting to fuse country music and rap. Finally, Ed attends a Tea Party convention, to share with those in attendance what he has learned. Last in the series(n)

programme.title: Lost Boys? What's Going Wrong for Asian Men
programme.desc: Reporter Mehreen Baig reports on the challenges facing Asian men growing up in modern Britain. She begins in Bradford, a city where man of Pakistani heritage are experiencing high levels of youth unemployment, failing education and drug crime. In Leicester, she explores the Gujarati community, and discovers a history of entrepreneurship that has contributed to greater integration. Finally, she travels to Kashmir and meets a grandfather who was one of the first wave of immigrants to Britain in the 1960s(n)

programme.title: Kings of Curry
programme.desc: Two brothers who are both chefs fall out, and decide to split their family recipe book in two, opening competing restaurants on the same street. After 20 years of rivalry, the daughter of one of the pair is determined to reconcile her father and uncle so they can both attend her wedding. Comedy, starring Amara Karan and Harish Patel(n)

programme.title: Countryfile
programme.desc: The show comes from East Yorkshire, where John Craven meets Bridlington residents who take traditional coble boats out to sea, Margherita Taylor uncovers a secret art trail in the Wolds and meets poet Ian MacMillan, and Steve Brown learns about different uses for hemp. Plus, Charlotte Smith reports on the impact of tourism on beauty spots and Adam Henson meets a farmer with an active online presence(n)

programme.title: Holby City
programme.desc: Fletch clashes with estranged father Steven when Evie demands they let him back into their lives, while Essie is determined to help Josh after discovering he was an applicant for Gaskell's Project Laszlo. Dominic fears for his compatibility with Lofty after a contagious incident on AAU shows they are not thinking the same way(n)

programme.title: An Island Parish
programme.sub-title: Island Parish Sark Winter: 'Tis the Season
programme.desc: Documentary chronicling life on Sark in the Channel Islands, beginning with the residents making preparations for Christmas. Julie installs lifesize handmade elves in her shop, fisherman Baz Adams distributes vast quantities of mistletoe and Methodist lay preacher Karen Le Mouton calls in some help for a special service(n)

programme.title: Animal Park Summer Special
programme.desc: Kate Humble and Ben Fogle join the keepers fighting to save the life of the last remaining cheetah cub and discover a thief on the loose at a family farmyard. Across the park, a team rushes to the aid of Steph, an elderly and much-loved zebra, who is being violently bullied by the rest of the herd(n)

programme.title: Impossible
programme.desc: Rick Edwards hosts the game show in which 24 recurring contestants compete for the chance to win a £10,000 jackpot, with a single `impossible' answer knocking them out for the day. Last in the series(n)

programme.title: Antiques Roadshow
programme.desc: Fiona Bruce presents the show from Trelissick House and gardens in Cornwall. Items brought in to be valued include an ejector seat from a Vulcan bomber, a miniature sewing kit, and a gold snuff box with a connection to DH Lawrence(n)

programme.title: Victoria Derbyshire
programme.desc: Daily news and current-affairs programme offering discussion of breaking stories, exclusive interviews and audience interaction via social media(n)

programme.title: BBC Newsroom Live
programme.desc: A chance to stay up to date on the day's leading stories, with the latest breaking news as it happens(n)

programme.title: Angels One Five
programme.desc: A new recruit joins a squadron of British fighter pilots in the summer of 1940, as they prepare to face a confrontation with the overwhelming forces of the Luftwaffe over the English Channel, while the ground crew at their base anxiously awaits reports from the conflict. Second World War adventure, starring Jack Hawkins and John Gregson(n)

programme.title: Talking Pictures
programme.desc: Sylvia Syms revisits some of the great British war films that helped boost the nation's morale in the difficult years that followed the end of the Second World War. Among the silver screen gems highlighted are In Which We Serve, Reach for the Sky, Bridge on the River Kwai and The Dam Busters. The programme includes archive interviews with stars including Noel Coward, Richard Attenborough, David Lean, Alec Guinness, Kenneth More and John Mills, and Sylvia shares her memories of filming her own contribution to the genre, Ice Cold in Alex(n)

programme.title: 24 Hours in the Past
programme.desc: Living reality documentary in which six celebrities travel back in time to the 19th century, spending four full days experiencing the relentless graft of the working poor in Victorian Britain. Impressionist Alistair McGowan, former minister Ann Widdecombe, actress Zoe Lucker, world champion hurdler Colin Jackson, actor Tyger Drew-Honey and presenter Miquita Oliver are the volunteers, whose first 24 hours lands them in the dustyard, where they have to sift through mountains of dirt, rotting veg and old bones. Presented by Fi Glover, with historian Ruth Goodman(n)

programme.title: Nature's Weirdest Events
programme.desc: Chris Packham investigates more unusual natural events with the aid of eyewitness accounts and film clips, featuring a crab milked for its blue blood, stones that mysteriously move by themselves across the desert and a Japanese island swarming with rabbits(n)

programme.title: Oceans
programme.desc: A team of marine experts reveal the hidden stories of our planet's last true wilderness - its oceans. Here, they investigate how the predatory Humboldt squid is invading the sea(n)

programme.title: Antiques Road Trip
programme.desc: Experts Raj Bisram and Catherine Southon set off on a search for items in Cambridgeshire, heading for an auction showdown in the Suffolk market town of Beccles(n)

programme.title: Celebrity Eggheads
programme.desc: New series. Stars of the small screen Jeremy Edwards, Chizzy Akudolu, Susie Amy, Mark Little and Hayley Tamaddon take on the general-knowledge champions to win a cash prize for charity. Jeremy Vine asks the questions(n)

programme.title: The Repair Shop
programme.desc: New series. More family heirlooms are restored, including a watch hidden in the original owner's dress while she was a PoW, and a Louis Vuitton trunk that has seen better days(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: New series. The contest returns with chefs compete for a chance to show off their culinary skills at a banquet celebrating 70 years of the NHS, beginning with three contestants from the North East region. Returning competitor Danny Parker is joined by newcomers Dan Fletcher and David Coulson as they attempt to impress their surprise Great British menu veteran judge with their starters(n)

programme.title: Nadiya's Family Favourites
programme.desc: Nadiya Hussain demonstrates quick recipes for days when everything is a bit hectic, including mango and lime lassi bircher, a spin on prawn toast, seafood crumble, and a simple apple Rocky Road recipe. Nadiya's love for the simplicity of cereal takes her to the world's first cereal cafe in London, and her appreciation for bread sees her meet passionate baker Heather and the members of her club(n)

programme.title: University Challenge
programme.desc: In the fourth of the academic quiz's first-round matches, four students from SOAS, University of London, pit their wits against a team from Darwin College, Cambridge, in a bid to reach the second stage of the competition. Jeremy Paxman asks the questions(n)

programme.title: Bollywood: The World's Biggest Film Industry
programme.desc: Part one of two. Anita Rani explores the world of Indian cinema, revealing the extraordinary stories and secrets behind an industry that employs more than a quarter of a million people. She begins her journey in Mumbai - the home of Bollywood - where the stars tower over the city on enormous murals. Anita discovers just how important the movies are to everyday people at one of the city's oldest cinemas, where she quickly finds herself in the middle of a screaming mob as the cast of that night's film make a surprise appearance(n)

programme.title: The Wedding Guru

programme.desc: A salty curmudgeon who is discontentment with how his life has stalled is shocked to discover he has a now-teenage daughter put up for adoption by his ex-wife after their split. He tries to reunite the family, but his abrasive personality makes getting reacquainted unpleasant for everyone

programme.title: Addicted to Love
programme.desc: Good-natured astronomer Sam is devastated when the love of his life, Linda, leaves him for a suave Frenchman named Anton. He therefore does what every other normal dumpee would do; go to New York and set up home in the abandoned building opposite his exgirlfriend's apartment, intent on winning her back and waiting until she decides to leave her current lover. What Sam does not count on is being joined several weeks later by ultra hip tomboy Maggie, a photographer and motorcyclist who is determined to get revenge on Anton, her ex-fiance. Hostile at first, the two of them eventually join forces in an attempt to separate the couple, and ruin Anton's life. However, complications ensue when Sam and Maggie start falling for each other

programme.title: Everything Must Go
programme.desc: An alcoholic businessman holds a garage sale after being fired from his job and thrown out of the house along with his belongings by his fed-up wife. While living on his front lawn, he unexpectedly makes friends with a neighbourhood kid and tries to reconnect with a girl he loved in high school

programme.title: Honey
programme.desc: A dancer tries to balance her dreams of stardom with her devotion to her old neighborhood. Rappers Missy Elliott, Ginuwine and Jadakiss have cameos

programme.title: Ghosts of Girlfriends Past
programme.desc: Successful fashion photographer and confirmed womanizer Connor Mead (Matthew McConaughey) has learned everything he knows about women from his deceased uncle Wayne (Michael Douglas). As his brother is about to get married, Connor takes a break from his playboy lifestyle to attend the ceremony not without first trying to convince his sibling of the enormous mistake he is about to make. After a drunken speech at the rehearsal dinner, Connor meets in the bathroom the ghost of Uncle Wayne, who surprisingly shows his regret and tells his nephew that, over the course of the evening, he'll be visited by three ghosts who will lead him through his romantic past, present, and future. Will this be Connor¿s big chance to get over himself and find true love?

programme.title: The Layover
programme.desc: Two girlfriends go on vacation to get away from their problems. But when a hurricane warning results in a long layover in St. Louis, they end up competing for the attention of a hunky fellow passenger

programme.title: Bad Company
programme.desc: When CIA agents Oakes and Pope try to secure a suitcase-sized nuke from a black-market dealer, they are ambushed and Pope is killed. Desperate for the bad guys to believe that Pope is still alive, Oakes recruits Pope's long-lost twin, a petty criminal

programme.title: Elizabeth
programme.desc: Cate Blanchett reprises her role as Queen Elizabeth I in this account of her efforts to defend England from King Philip II of Spain, while trying to suppress her attraction to the dashing Sir Walter Raleigh

programme.title: Something's Gotta Give
programme.desc: Harry is an aging Casanova who refuses to accept his old age and Erica is an acclaimed dramatist. Certain unavoidable circumstances force them to share a roof, even though they are so different

programme.title: The American President
programme.desc: Andrew Shepherd is approaching the end of his first term as President of the United States. He's a widower with a young daughter and has proved to be popular with the public. His election seems assured. That is until he meets Sydney Ellen Wade, a paid political activist working for an environmental lobby group. He's immediately smitten with her and after several amusing attempts, they finally manage to go on a date (which happens to be a State dinner for the visiting President of France). His relationship with Wade opens the door for his prime political opponent, Senator Bob Rumson, to launch an attack on the President's character, something he could not do in the previous election as Shepherd's wife had only recently died

programme.title: A Walk in the Clouds
programme.desc: Alfonso Arau's delight of a romantic film, made after Like Water for Chocolate, opens with Paul Sutton returning home after World War II to a wife he married the day before he left. Discovering they have nothing in common, he leaves for home by bus. Among the passengers is Victoria Aragón, who is afraid to go home to her family's vineyards because she is pregnant and unmarried. Paul suggests they pretend to be a married couple, to conceal her situation. When they arrive at her home, her father Alberto and his wife María are stern and suspicious, as is patriarch Don Pedro, but as the days stretch into weeks, Paul falls for Victoria, her family and their way of life... Edited for content

programme.title: John Wick
programme.desc: Hit man John Wick is once again called out of retirement, this time by a former colleague who wants him to repay a debt by killing an Italian crime lord. But when the assassination goes awry, Wick finds himself hunted by an international cabal of killers, and his only hope for survival might be a shadowy figure known as the Bowery King

programme.title: The Client
programme.desc: An 11-year-old boy, who has witnessed a suicide, hires an attorney to protect himself and his family from mobsters

programme.title: Jackie
programme.desc: In the immediate aftermath of the assassination of President John F. Kennedy, his wife Jacqueline deals with her immense grief while caring for her young family and making plans for his funeral procession. At the same time, a bereaved nation watches on

programme.title: The Mummy
programme.desc: A soldier discovers the tomb of a female pharaoh named Ahmanet during a firefight in the Middle East. But when he and a British Egyptologist excavate the findings, the resurrected Ahmanet emerges from her sarcophagus with a plot to enslave humanity

programme.title: Sideways
programme.desc: (2004) In Alexander Payne's bittersweet comedy, two buddies, Miles (Paul Giamatti) and Jack (Thomas Haden Church), embark on Jack's stag week, a tasting trip around California's wine country, with wine buff Miles leading the way. Miles may be a wine expert but he's also a bitter divorcee, depressed and in love with a waitress, Maya (VIrginia Marsden), whose presence always leaves him tongue-tied. Jack is a faded actor who can't quite resign himself to marriage when there are still obtainable women in the world, married or not, and when he meets Stephanie (Sandra Oh) at a tasting, he swears Miles to secrecy about the wedding. And so the foursome continue their trip... Alexander Payne's Oscar and BAFTA-winning road trip is a classic of friendship and crisis, with four outstanding leads

programme.title: Born on the Fourth of July

programme.title: Lara Croft Tomb Raider
programme.desc: In this sequel to Lara Croft: Tomb Raider, British archaeologist Lara Croft (Angelina Jolie) has made an important archaeological discovery: an orb that leads to the mythical Pandora's Box. Unfortunately, mad scientist Jonathan Reiss is also after the box willing to open it as his ultimate weapon. Recruited by British Intelligence, Croft will go into a journey that includes Hong Kong, Kenya, Tanzania, Greece and China, to stop the evil Reiss and save the world

programme.title: Inherent Vice
programme.desc: In this offbeat detective story set in 1970 California, a drug-addled private eye investigates a conspiracy involving his ex-flame and her married, real-estate-developer boyfriend. Meanwhile, various eccentric characters complicate the investigation

programme.title: Our Family Wedding
programme.desc: Lance Gross and Ugly Betty star America Ferrara take the lead roles in this warring-families romcom directed by Rick Famuyiwa. Latina Lucia Ramirez and African American Marcus Boyd met and fell in love while they were in college. Marcus has now graduated from Columbia Medical School and is due to take up a post in Laos, so the couple - who have been living together and got engaged without telling their respective families - have decided the time is right to tie the knot. However, this comes as an unpleasant surprise to the lovers' fathers, who have already met under unfortunate circumstances and traded racial abuse with each other. Can Lucia and Marcus calm things down before their big day? Well, even if they do, they'll also have to contend with a goat that has consumed a certain brand of little blue pills and whose libido has gone through the roof... Also starring Forest Whitaker and Latino comedian Carlos Mencia as the two ill-tempered and competitive dads

programme.title: About a Boy
programme.desc: Adaptation of the Nick Hornby novel about the friendship that develops between a bright but awkward 12-year-old boy and a wayward thirtysomething man masquerading as a lone parent in a bid to seduce single mothers. Ironically, it is the boy who initiates the bachelor into the world of adult responsibility and meaningful relationships as the bond between them deepens

Balian, as well as falling for Baldwin's sister Sibylla (Eva Green), finds himself a power broker between the two factions, with the fate of the city in his hands. Michael Caton-Jones' thriller racks up the tension as it follows the parallel paths of the hunter and the assassin with the clock ticking down in this re-make of The Day of the Jackal

programme.title: He's Just Not That Into You
programme.desc: An adaptation of a best-selling self-help book, 'He's Just Not That Into You' follows the story of a group who tries to sort out the signals that the sexes exchange. Gigi (Ginnifer Goodwin) imagines every man she meets is Mr. Right. She gets advice from a bar owner (Justin Long) who prides himself on understanding the ins and outs of the dating scene. Her friend Janine (Jennifer Connelly) seems to have a solid marriage with Ben (Bradley Cooper). Until he meets the attractive Anna (Scarlett Johansson), who's indifferent to Conor's (Kevin Connolly) pursuits. Another friend of Gigi's, Beth (Jennifer Aniston), enjoys a successful seven-year relationship with Neil (Ben Affleck), but dumps him when she realizes that he has no interest in getting married. Lastly, Mary (Drew Barrymore) is an advertising professional who tries to find love online. Will they finally figure out who is and who isn't into them?

programme.desc: Liam Neeson stars as former CIA operative Bryan Mills, who's desperate to track down his kidnapped daughter in Pierre Morel's Luc Besson-produced action-thriller. Mills' life hasn't panned out well; his dedication to the CIA wrecked his marriage and made him neglect his daughter Kim. Now, retired from the Agency, he wants to make things up to Kim. But to do so, he has to contend with his ex-wife's animosity and Kim's new step-father's wealth. So when he has an opportunity to advance Kim's pop star ambitions he jumps at the chance, even if that means her and a friend crossing the Atlantic to brave 'the dangers of Europe'. As things turn out, he has a point: in Paris, the two girls are kidnapped by vicious Eastern European sex traffickers. As they are being abducted, Bryan tells one of the baddies, via Kim's mobile phone: 'I will look for you, I will find you, and I will kill you'. He subsequently does his best to make good on his promise, using all the violent tricks of the trade his time at the CIA taught him

The objective is to create a legion of powerful soldiers to conquer Mars. But the experiment goes wrong and Banner's organism is affected by the gamma rays. Now, every time the scientist gets angry, he turns into Hulk, a gigantic green beast with an astounding, uncontrollable strength. To prevent anyone from getting hurt, especially his loved one, Betsy Ross (Jennifer Connelly), the scientist tries to move away from the city. They met at an auction in Nantucket one rainswept afternoon seventeen years ago, bidding against each other for the same ivory figurine, and instantly fell in love. He was a brilliant law student at Harvard, and she, a college girl and star gymnast. They were soon married and had two wonderful children. As Oliver becomes more successful, his recognition of his wife's separate identity dwindles to the danger point. Although she has everything she could possibly want, Barbara wants more and decides to start a catering company which turns out to be a great success. She also begins to imagine life without Oliver and, finding the idea not entirely displeasing, decides to ask him for a divorce..

Unfortunately, the collector's shop is robbed by two small-time thieves and the detective loses his card. With no other choice, Paul and Jimmy end up going rogue, tracking down the card and the drug ring behind its theft, all on their own time, and without any backup -- except for each other

programme.desc: (2010) This family adventure from Chris Columbus (who directed the first two Harry Potter films) is adapted from the first of Rick Riordan's series of fantasy novels, and stars Logan Lerman as Percy Jackson, an American teen who finds that Greek myth is much closer to home than he imagined. It turns out that while his mum Sally (Catherine Keener) is human, his father (Kevin McKidd) is the Greek god of the sea and earthquakes, Poseidon; which makes our hero a demigod. At first it's all a bit much to take in, as he learns the modern world is teeming with deities and their offspring. And things take a turn for the worse when Zeus (Sean Bean) suspects Percy of theft after the lightning bolt that confers supreme, terrifying power goes missing. With his mother kidnapped and the errant super weapon threatening to cause a catastrophic clash of the gods, Percy sets off to recover the artefact. As he does so, he discovers the many creatures and monsters of legend are also alive today, and are as fierce as ever. Also starring Pierce Brosnan (as a centaur), Uma Thurman (as Medusa) and Steve Coogan (as Hades)

programme.title: Stratton

programme.title: The Fast and the Furious
programme.desc: Vin Diesel (Triple X) is Dominic Toretto, leader of a gang accused of stealing over a million dollars in electronic equipment. Packed with adrenaline, he makes a living transforming regular cars into powerful racing cars. With a stronghold on the streets of Los Angeles, nothing seems to stop him. Until a new King of Speed appears -undercover police officer Brian O'Conner, sent by the FBI to infiltrate the gang and find out who is responsible for the robberies. Quick and tough, Brian has enough experience and determination to become the winner on the roads. As he gains Dominic's confidence, he has everything to solve the case. In the process they become friends and Brian falls in love with Dominic's sister, Mia

programme.desc: Tsotsi and Rendition director Gavin Hood's fantasy adventure explores the backstory of the most hirsute and mercurial of the X-Men: Wolverine. The tale kicks off in 1845 with the incident that sparked the young James Howlett's initial mutation and his alliance with Victor Creed. Over the course of the next century the two immerse themselves in a series of major conflicts, right up to the Vietnam War, where they are recruited by Major Stryker to join Team X: a killing machine staffed by other mutants. Uncomfortable with the merciless, legally dubious methods the unit employs, Howlett leaves, seeking a quiet life. However, a violent, catastrophic incident turns Logan's world upside down, propelling him on a course that will result in confrontation with his former ally Creed, as well as Logan's final transmogrification into Wolverine. They become involved in a Jewish resistance fighter's plan to blow up the Parisian premiere of one of Goebbels' propaganda films - an event due to be attended by Hitler himself. programme.desc: In the mythical Middle-earth, a fantastic, mysterious world inhabited by men, Hobbits, wizards, elves, dwarfs and Trolls, lives Frodo Baggins (Elijah Wood), a shy Hobbit who must accomplish a difficult mission to save his land's destiny. It all begins when Frodo receives a ring from his uncle Bilbo (Ian Holm) and wizard Gandalf (Ian McKellen) discovers it is the Unique Ring itself. This powerful ring has been conceived by Sauron, the dark Lord of Mordor (Sala Baker), and with it, it is possible to enslave the whole of the Middle-earth through the use of dark forces. To destroy the ring, Frodo must take it to a distant mountain in Mordor, a region controlled by the Master of Evil. Fortunately, he is accompanied by a group formed by Hobbits Sam (Sean Astin), Merry (Dominic Monaghan) and Pippin (Billy Boyd), as well as Gandalf, the human warriors Aragorn (Viggo Mortensen) and Boromir (Sean Bean), and elf Legolas (Orlando Bloom). Together they have to confront dangerous obstacles in a frightening world of mystery and darkness. This spectacular adaptation of J.R.R. Tolkien's epic trilogy was directed by Peter Jackson

programme.title: Almost Famous
programme.desc: Written and directed by Cameron Crowe, Almost Famous tells the story of a 15-year-old boy who, in the early '70s, is given the opportunity to go on tour with a rock band. William Miller's mother is overly obsessed with drugs and the negative influence of rock on teenagers. But he is a music lover and his hobby is to write about bands for an underground newspaper. The boy's work eventually catches the attention of Lester Bangs (Philip Seymor Hoffman), editor of a rock magazine who then asks him to cover a great concert. William manages to get only an interview with the opening band, Stillwater, but even so he wins the admiration of another editor, this time, of Rolling Stone. Now the boy has the opportunity to continue traveling with Stillwater and write an article that could open up the way to showbiz. During the tour he meets various interesting people, including a girl he falls in love with (Kate Hudson). Crowe, who received an Oscar for Best Screenplay for this film, wrote the story based on his teenage experiences, when he also contributed to Rolling Stone

programme.desc: Georgia (12-1) vs. Oklahoma (12-1). From the Rose Bowl in Pasadena, Cal. At QB, Tide sophomore Jalen Hurts has thrown one INT all season and looks to improve on his 13-for-31 night vs. Clemson last year. Tigers junior Kelly Bryant (24 total TDs) operates behind three first-team All-ACC linemen
